JS ->
    It is an object based client side scripting lang.
    It is an interprator lang.
    It is a case sensitive lang.
    It has errors
    It can not run directly
    It is used to given funcationalities to the website
    It is a loosely/dynamic type lang.

    JS Engine

        1. Chrome/Edge/Chro/Brave -> V8
        2. Firefox -> Spider Monkey
        3. I.E -> Chakra


    Types ->
        1. Internal
            <script>
                code
            </script>
        2. External (.js)

            <script src=".js"></script>


    How TO Print In JS ->
    document.write('hello')
    

    Variables ->
        A Temporary Memory Location where we store our value
        and value may be vary

        How To Create A Variable ->
            var variablename=value

            Rules Of variablename ->
                1. never use number
                2. never use space
                3. never use symbols exception _
    
    Data Types ->

        1. String -> '' or ""
        2. Number -> 3 or 3.9
        3. Boolean -> true(1) or false(0)
        4. Array -> []
        5. Object -> {}
        6. undefined
        7. null
        8. NaN -> Not A Number


    Arthematic Op. ->
        +,-,*,/
        % (modulas)
        ** (exponential)

    Comments ->

        1. // single line
        2. /* multi line  */

    Comparison ->
        >,<,>=,<=

        == (Equal To -> Check value only)

        === (Identical -> Check value and data type )


    Logical Op ->
        1. AND -> && -> if all true result true
        2. OR -> || -> if one true result true
        3. NOT -> ! -> Opposite

    
    Concatenation ->
        joining of multiple values
        +


    Increment / Decrement ->
        Post -> next line
        a++ => a+1
        a-- => a-1

        Pre -> same line
        ++a => a+1



    Conditions ->
        single
        1. if
            Syntax ->
                if(Comparison){
                    statement
                }

        2. if else
            Syntax ->
                if(Comparison){
                    statement
                }else{
                    statement
                }

        Multi
        3. if else if

            Syntax ->
                if(Comparison){
                    statement
                }else if(Comparison1){
                    statement1
                }
                .
                .
                else{
                    statement
                }


        4. switch

            Syntax ->

                switch(expression){
                    case Comparison:
                    statement
                    break
                    case Comparison:
                    statement
                    break
                    .
                    .
                    .
                    default:
                    statement
                }


    Loops ->
        1. for
            Syntax ->
                for(init.;Comparison;inc/dec){
                    statement
                }

        2. while

            Syntax ->
            init;
            while(Comparison){
                statement
                inc/dec
            }

        3. do while

            Syntax ->
            init;
            do{
                statement
                inc/dec
            }while(Comparison)



    String Methods ->
        1. length
        2. toUpperCase()
        3. toLowerCase()
        4. search()
        5. replace()
        6. slice()
        7. split() -> converts string into array
        8. lastIndexOf()
        9. indexOf()
        10. charAt()
        11. charCodeAt()
        12. substr()
        13. substring()
        14. trim()
        

    Number Methods ->  
        1. parseInt()
        2. parseFloat()
    
    Math Methods ->
        1. abs()
        2. round()
        3. floor()
        4. ceil()
        5. random()


1. otp => 6 digit
2. random string => 6 digit

    Array Methods ->
        1. length

        LIFO -> Last In First Out
        2. push()
        3. pop()
        
        FIFO -> First In First Out
        4. shift()
        5. unshift()
        
        
        
        6. splice()
        7. join()
        8. concat()
        9. delete
        10. toString()

BOM -> Browser/Box Object Model
    Pop up boxes

    1. alert()
    2. confirm()
    3. prompt()


DOM ->
    Document Object Model

    








Storage =>

    1. client Storage
        1. cookies
            name value and time pair
            4kb

        2. localStorage
            5mb with no time limit

            1. write
                localStorage.setItem('name','value')
            
            2. read
                localStorage.getItem('name')
            
            3. remove
                localStorage.removeItem('name')

    2. Physical Storage -> DB



Methods ->
    1. GET
    2. POST
    3. PUT/PATCH
    4. DELETE















